attributes.descriptionHtml:
Scotty is a drop dead gorgeous orange/red classic tabby. "Classic" refers to those gorgeous circular spiral swirls of color. He is a timid young man and will need lots of time, quiet and patience. We'll be happy to help you work through it.
He's actually made a lot of progress. Everyone who met him at the vet talks about sweet he is. He even likes belly rubs. But still he's a little guy that should start off in a room by himself, with a hidey hole, food, water and litter all to himself while he bonds with his forever purrson. Not a good choice for a home with chidren or dogs. FELV/FIV negative, shots, altered. Will be microchipped prior to adoption. Adoption fee includes registering the microchip. For more information call Lil at 410-679-2125 or email her at lildecker1@aol.com (but be patient, Lil isn't an email person and doesn't check email every 15 minutes like some of us).

attributes.descriptionHtml: Pretty Boy came from one of our colonies.  Some of these photos were while he was still outside  The vet estimates he's 4-8 years old.  He's a big, solid boy.  I call him lilac point on white.  Light blue, quite crossed, Siamese eyes. He's been outside awhile, we don't know how long.  But we've promised him an indoor forever home!  He's FELV/FIV negative, neutered, vaccinated and microchipped.  He also had extensive dental work.  So he's completely vetted and ready to roll!   He's not a youngster but has looks and purrsonality to spare.  Every time I'd go to feed the colony he'd run up to greet me and "escort" me back to the feeding station. I just couldn't leave him out there. Excellent vet references and adoption fee required.  For more information email catresuceofmd@mindspring.com.

attributes.descriptionHtml: I picked up (literally, no trap required) Indy on July 3 so named her for Independence Day.  She had been outside at least a year.  When I started feeding these colonies (as a substitute for a woman who is quite ill) Indy is the ONLY cat who was more interested in attention from me than in the food  (although she likes food, too).  She had cherry eye (if you have a strong stomach and want to see it in color, check google).  We had her to the opthalmologist who did surgery and all indications are the surgery was successful.  She's also spayed, vaccinated and micrcochipped.  She's probably about 2 years old.  She is tiny and quiet and timid but just loves her chin rubbed and sitting on laps.  She will be best suited for someone with a relatively quiet household, I think.  Indoor only, of course.  She has suffered through her last snowstorm outside!  Excellent vet references and adoption fee required.  For more information contact catrescueofmd@mindspring.com
